<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-09-24T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-09-24T22:00:00-05:00" n="35" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d35">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">710.G Commercial Agreement/39:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-09-24T22:00:00-05:00">September 24, 1934—10
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 25—3:17 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>75. Your circular of September 23, 2 p.m. Officials of the Colombian
                            Ministry for Foreign Affairs whom I have consulted fail to see any
                            advantage to be derived for Colombia from the Agreement which was opened
                            for signature by the Pan American Union on July 15. <pb facs="0090" n="20" xml:id="pg_20"/> If the Department deems it desirable to
                            suggest any arguments, I can transmit them to responsible officials.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>